        {
          "insert": "Expand:",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " an exact lattice — one shared cell extent, one ladder gap, column and row identity preserved. Template members are pixel-identical in the corpus: every cell in ink's 3x4 table is exactly 288x80, and gc's five config pills are exactly 288x64, so the expander gives all cells one extent and one scale and the registers survive exactly. Grid cells are immovable afterwards — no align shift, fan pitch, or overlap push may move a lattice cell; the lattice anchors those constraints instead."
        }
